What is a component?
it is a modular portable replaceable and reusable set of functionality.
it is a software object intended to interact with other components
What are the charactistics of a component?
reusability
replaceable
not context specific
extensible
encapsulated
independent

What are the advantages of using component based architecture?
ease of deployment
reduced componentsease of development
reusable
modification of technical complexity
reliability
system maintenance and evolution
independent


What is props short for?
it stands for properties 

How are props used in React?
they are used for passing data from one component to another

What is the flow of props?
props data is read only so the data coming from the parent should not be changed by child components.




#class 1

classes are used to group together chunks of code so that you can reuse it in lots of places. You can extend classes with another class to create answers to different situations

